On International Holocaust Remembrance Day, the article reflects on the millions of lives lost during the Holocaust and renews the commitment to fight against anti-Semitism. This year is particularly significant as it marks the 75th anniversary of the liberation of Auschwitz. The article acknowledges the heroes who risked their lives to help liberate the camps and emphasizes the importance of never repeating such atrocities. The article also mentions the ongoing persecution and discrimination faced by Jewish individuals today and highlights an Executive Order issued in December 2019 to combat anti-Semitic discrimination in the United States. The article concludes by urging unity against intolerance and oppression, and the need to combat evil and oppressive regimes with democracy, justice, and compassion.